ement and dispersal of respiratory hazards. In so doing, they reveal how an aesthetic attention to breathing generates historically, culturally, and environmentally situated tactics and strategies for living under precarity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aArts and society. 0aEcocriticism. 0aEnvironment (Aesthetics) 0aEnvironment (Aesthetics). 0aFeminism and the arts. 0aQueer theory. 0aRespiration in art. 0aRespiration in literature. 0aRespirationxPolitical aspects. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023494?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023494423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023494/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles